<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Gmail on Tech Notebook</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/tags/gmail/</link><description>Recent content in Gmail on Tech Notebook</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Thu, 01 May 2025 20:33:41 +0200</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://wiki.deimos.fr/tags/gmail/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Gmail: Having Multiple Email Addresses with a Single Gmail Account</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Gmail_:_Avoir_plusieurs_adresses_mails_avec_un_seul_compte_gmail/</link><pubDate>Sun, 09 Dec 2007 12:14:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Gmail_:_Avoir_plusieurs_adresses_mails_avec_un_seul_compte_gmail/</guid><description>&lt;p>You might want to have multiple email addresses without having multiple accounts. For example, one address for your newsletters, one disposable address, and so on.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>You can use the &amp;ldquo;+&amp;rdquo; sign to accomplish this, for example:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;a href="mailto:youremail@gmail.com" rel="external" target="_blank">youremail@gmail.com&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a>: your main address&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;a href="mailto:youremail+trash@gmail.com" rel="external" target="_blank">youremail+trash@gmail.com&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a>: your disposable address&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;a href="mailto:youremail+newsletters@gmail.com" rel="external" target="_blank">youremail+newsletters@gmail.com&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a>: your address for newsletters&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>This gives you multiple addresses, but all emails will arrive in the same inbox. You can then create filtering rules to sort them into specific folders for automated organization.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>